data.title: Boleslaus I, Duke of Bohemia
data.meta_description: Boleslaus I, a member of the PÅ™emyslid dynasty, was ruler of the Duchy of Bohemia from 935 until his death in 972. He is notorious for the murder of his elder brother Wenceslaus, through which he became duke.
